						<summary>

						<p>The stone is mutilated and a few words in the beginning of every line are lost. The date of the record is also lost. It refers itself to the reign of the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva</hi> and mentions his feudatory <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla-Vīra-Pāṇḍyadēva</hi> as ruling over <hi rend="bold">•• • • • • thirtytwothousand</hi> province. The latter's queen is said to be of the <hi rend="bold">Chandragupta</hi> family.</p>						

						</summary>
